<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="645" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d645">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox,
                                        Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-30"><hi rend="italic">July 30,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Can you inform me whether United States Government intend to demand
                            extradition of Harry L. Holmes, now held at Montreal for theft?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Durand.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>